d an audience. Honour was inevitably gendered and performative, and as such, it functioned as one of the overarching metrics of value that early modern men and women applied to themselves and others. In charting how non-elite subjects rendered their lives legitimate through autobiography, Arms and Letters contributes both to a critical genealogy of honour and to the history of life writing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAutobiography. 0aHonor in literature. 0aHonorzSpainxHistory. 0aMilitary biography. 0aSoldierszSpainxBiographyxHistory and criticism. 0aSoldiers' writings, SpanishxHistory and criticism. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Spain & Portugal.2bisacsh  aRenaissance.  aSpanish literature.  aautobiography.  achivalric.  aearly modern.  ahonor.  ahonour.  alife.  aliterature.  amemoirs.  amilitary.  anovel.  apicaresque novel.  aself-fashioning.  asoldiers.  awar.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753544540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487535445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487535445/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  